<subSubSection id="C339C3A04919FFC7FF31FE2266AF3A27" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B9C902B4919FFC7FF31FE2267163D38" blockId="1.[151,1436,405,1357]" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="B9574C394919FFC7FF31FE2264443EC5" bold="true" box="[151,279,405,431]" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FE04FE22674D3EC4" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1896" box="[418,542,405,430]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Smerdalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9574C394919FFC7FE04FE22674D3EC4" box="[418,542,405,430]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">Smerdalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will run to 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FD0AFE22666F3EC5" authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1929" box="[684,828,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Stegaspidini">Stegaspidini</taxonomicName>
in the tribal key of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB2EDDA4919FFC7FB8CFE2260773EC5" author="Dietrich, C. H. &amp; McKamey, S. H. &amp; Deitz, L. L." box="[1066,1316,405,431]" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" pagination="213 - 239" refId="ref5559" refString="Dietrich, C. H., McKamey, S. H. &amp; Deitz, L. L. (2001) Morphology-based phylogeny of the treehopper family Membracidae (Hemiptera: Cicadomorpha: Membracoidea). Systematic Entomology, 26, 213 - 239." type="journal article" year="2001">
Dietrich 
<emphasis id="B9574C394919FFC7FB35FE22619D3EC4" box="[1171,1230,405,430]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
but differ from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FEBCFE0A64F93EBD" authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1929" box="[282,426,445,471]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Stegaspidini">Stegaspidini</taxonomicName>
in having the pronotum with a pair of suprahumeral horns and a distally enlarged posterior pronotal process bearing three or more spines; the forewing with crossvein m-cu 
<subScript id="17A7926E4919FFC7FB2FFE4261C23D69" attach="left" box="[1161,1169,501,515]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">2</subScript>
joining M distad of its fork, and the first anal vein contacting the claval suture for a short distance preapically; and the hind tibia with cucullate setal row I well developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9C902B4919FFC7FF60FDD764813B97" blockId="1.[151,1436,405,1357]" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="B9574C394919FFC7FF60FDD764403D10" bold="true" box="[198,275,608,634]" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">Notes.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB2EDDA4919FFC7FEBDFDD764E33D10" author="Deitz, L. L." box="[283,432,608,634]" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 177" refId="ref5481" refString="Deitz, L. L. (1975) Classification of the higher categories of the New World treehoppers (Homoptera: Membracidae). North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station Technical Bulletin, 225, 1 - 177." type="journal article" year="1975">Deitz (1975)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FDACFDD767D53D13" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1896" box="[522,646,608,633]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Smerdalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9574C394919FFC7FDACFDD767D53D13" box="[522,646,608,633]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">Smerdalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FD0DFDD7661E3D10" baseAuthorityName="Cryan and Deitz" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[683,845,608,634]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Stegaspidinae">Stegaspidinae</taxonomicName>
(as Stegaspinae) based on the acuminate forewing clavus, exposed scutellum, and lack of abdominal punctation. He included it in his tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FB16FD3F60023DC8" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[1200,1361,648,674]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Microcentrini">Microcentrini</taxonomicName>
based on the presence of dorsal preapical setae on the hind femur and three cucullate setal rows on the hind tibia. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB2EDDA4919FFC7FF31FD6F642A3D98" author="Cryan, J. R. &amp; Deitz, L. L. &amp; Robinson, J." box="[151,377,728,754]" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" refId="ref5359" refString="Cryan, J. R., Deitz, L. L. &amp; Robinson, J. (2003) The Neotropical treehopper tribe Microcentrini (Hemiptera: Membracidae): monographic revision and phylogenetic position. Thomas Say Publications (Entomological Society of America), Lanham, Maryland, iii + 108 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Cryan 
<emphasis id="B9574C394919FFC7FF41FD6F64703D9B" box="[231,291,728,753]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
transferred the genus to 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FD05FD6F66653D98" authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1929" box="[675,822,728,754]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Stegaspidini">Stegaspidini</taxonomicName>
, citing the presence of a single r-m crossvein in the forewing, the absence of an articulated dorsally hooked lateral plate on the male genital capsule, and the results of a morphology-based phylogenetic analysis, which grouped 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FC76FC9F611F3C2B" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1896" box="[976,1100,808,833]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Smerdalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9574C394919FFC7FC76FC9F611F3C2B" box="[976,1100,808,833]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">Smerdalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with other members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FACBFC9F64553C00" authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1929" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Stegaspidini">Stegaspidini</taxonomicName>
. However, placement of the genus within 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FD56FCE766C13C00" baseAuthorityName="Cryan and Deitz" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[752,914,848,874]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Stegaspidinae">Stegaspidinae</taxonomicName>
depends, at least in part, on interpretation of the position of the distal m-cu crossvein in 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FD32FCCF66433CFB" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1896" box="[660,784,888,913]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Smerdalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9574C394919FFC7FD32FCCF66433CFB" box="[660,784,888,913]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">Smerdalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(i.e., connected to vein M distad of its fork) as a reversal (character 29 state 2 of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB2EDDA4919FFC7FE77FC1767CE3CD0" author="Cryan, J. R. &amp; Deitz, L. L. &amp; Robinson, J." box="[465,669,928,954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" refId="ref5359" refString="Cryan, J. R., Deitz, L. L. &amp; Robinson, J. (2003) The Neotropical treehopper tribe Microcentrini (Hemiptera: Membracidae): monographic revision and phylogenetic position. Thomas Say Publications (Entomological Society of America), Lanham, Maryland, iii + 108 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Cryan 
<emphasis id="B9574C394919FFC7FD86FC1767093CD3" box="[544,602,928,953]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
) rather than a plesiomorphy shared with non-stegaspidines (character 29 state 0). Also, because the forewing venation and hind tibial chaetotaxy of 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FB34FC7F605D3C8B" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1896" box="[1170,1294,968,993]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Smerdalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9574C394919FFC7FB34FC7F605D3C8B" box="[1170,1294,968,993]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">Smerdalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of all other 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FECFFC4764AA3B60" authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1929" box="[361,505,1008,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Stegaspidini">Stegaspidini</taxonomicName>
(other genera of the tribe lack cucullate setal row I on the hind tibia and have crossvein m-cu 
<subScript id="17A7926E4919FFC7FEEFFB9F64023B5C" attach="left" box="[329,337,1064,1078]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">2</subScript>
joining M basad of its fork), placement of 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FCE8FBAF66993B5B" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1896" box="[846,970,1048,1073]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Smerdalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9574C394919FFC7FCE8FBAF66993B5B" box="[846,970,1048,1073]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">Smerdalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this tribe should be considered tenuous at best. Indeed, the most extensive molecular phylogenetic analysis of 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FBBBFBF461ED3B37" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1815" box="[1053,1214,1091,1117]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Membracidae</taxonomicName>
to date (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB2EDDA4919FFC7FA8DFBF465803BEF" author="Lin, C. - P. &amp; Danforth, B. N. &amp; Wood, T. K." pageId="1" pageNumber="30" pagination="400 - 421" refId="ref5606" refString="Lin, C. - P., Danforth, B. N. &amp; Wood, T. K. (2004) Molecular phylogenetics and evolution of maternal care in membracine treehoppers. Systematic Biology, 53, 400 - 421." type="journal article" year="2004">
Lin 
<emphasis id="B9574C394919FFC7FAF9FBF460CF3B36" box="[1375,1436,1091,1116]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
2004
</bibRefCitation>
) placed 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FE9AFBDC64EB3BEE" authorityName="Fowler" authorityYear="1896" box="[316,440,1131,1156]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Smerdalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9574C394919FFC7FE9AFBDC64EB3BEE" box="[316,440,1131,1156]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">Smerdalea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as sister to a clade comprising 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FC98FBDC66B33BEF" baseAuthorityName="Cryan and Deitz" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[830,992,1131,1157]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Stegaspidinae">Stegaspidinae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FBB9FBDC61F83BEF" baseAuthorityName="Wallace and Deitz" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[1055,1195,1131,1157]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Centrotinae">Centrotinae</taxonomicName>
, suggesting that the genus represents a lineage distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FDD7FB2461143BC7" authority="sensu Cryan et al. (2003)" authorityName="Cryan" authorityYear="2003" box="[625,1095,1171,1197]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Stegaspidinae">
Stegaspidinae sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB2EDDA4919FFC7FCC5FB2461143BC7" author="Cryan, J. R. &amp; Deitz, L. L. &amp; Robinson, J." box="[867,1095,1171,1197]" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" refId="ref5359" refString="Cryan, J. R., Deitz, L. L. &amp; Robinson, J. (2003) The Neotropical treehopper tribe Microcentrini (Hemiptera: Membracidae): monographic revision and phylogenetic position. Thomas Say Publications (Entomological Society of America), Lanham, Maryland, iii + 108 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Cryan 
<emphasis id="B9574C394919FFC7FC14FB2466BE3BC6" box="[946,1005,1171,1196]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Discovery of the bizarre but apparently related genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FE6DFB0C67353BBE" authority="Dietrich, 2008" authorityName="Dietrich" authorityYear="2008" box="[459,614,1211,1236]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Smergotomia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="n. gen.">
<emphasis id="B9574C394919FFC7FE6DFB0C67353BBE" box="[459,614,1211,1236]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">Smergotomia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A264F1424919FFC7FDDEFB0C679F3BBF" box="[632,716,1211,1237]" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" rank="genus">n. gen.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, described below, seems to reinforce this interpretation (see notes under 
<taxonomicName id="4C23EBA84919FFC7FE80FB5464923B96" authorityName="Dietrich" authorityYear="2008" box="[294,449,1251,1276]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Smergotomia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
